# 5. What professors expect me to explain

### A modular system is easier to test because:
- Each module has a single responsibility  
- Modules can be replaced with stubs  
- Tests become isolated and predictable  
- I avoid side effects (UI, DB, network)  
- I can test logic without running the whole app  

### Example exam question:
"Why is modular design important for testing?"

Expected answer:
Because each module can be tested independently using stubs or mocks, without relying on real UI or database components. This makes tests faster, more reliable, and easier to maintain.

